1.3. Fit mô hình¶

In [ ]:
from sklearn.tree import DecisionTreeClassifier
from sklearn.model_selection import train_test_split

# To m hnh Decision Tree Classifier dng sklearn vi max_depth = 3, v criterion = 'gini'
dtree = DecisionTreeClassifier(max_depth=3,criterion='gini')

# Fit m hnh vi train data
dtree.fit(X_train, y_train)

# Predict trn train/test data dng m hnh  train
y_pred_train = dtree.predict(X_train)
y_pred_test =dtree.predict(X_test)

3. Model selection cho Decision Tree dùng phương pháp holdout¶

3.1. Chia dữ liệu¶

In [ ]:
# Chia d liu thnh 2 tp train_val v test set vi t l 80/2
X_train_val, X_test, y_train_val, y_test = train_test_split(
    oh_X, y, test_size = 0.2, random_state = 1)

# Tip theo, chia tp train_val thnh 2 tp train v validation set vi t l 75/25
X_train, X_val, y_train, y_val = train_test_split(
    X_train_val, y_train_val, test_size =0.25, random_state = 1)

3.2. Huấn luyện mô hình với các giá trị tham số max_depth khác nhau¶

In [ ]:
import numpy as np

# Create three lists for train, validation, and test F1-score
train_f1 = []
val_f1 = []
test_f1 = []

# List of hyper-parameter values 
depths = [1, 2, 3, 5, 10, 15]

# Loop over all the C values
for depth in depths:
    # To m hnh Logistic Ridge regression vi tham s C
    dtree = DecisionTreeClassifier(max_depth = depth)

    # Fit m hnh trn train data
    dtree.fit(X_train, y_train)
    
    # Predict trn train set 
    y_train_pred = dtree.predict(X_train)
    
    # Predict trn validation set 
    y_val_pred = dtree.predict(X_val)

    # Predict trn test set 
    y_test_pred = dtree.predict(X_test)
    
    # Tnh train, validation, v test F1-score
    f1_train = metrics.f1_score(y_true = y_train, y_pred = y_train_pred, average ='macro')
    f1_val = metrics.f1_score(y_true = y_val, y_pred = y_val_pred, average = 'macro')
    f1_test = metrics.f1_score(y_true = y_test, y_pred = y_test_pred, average ='macro')
    
    # Thm cc F1-score vo cc list tng ng
    train_f1.append(f1_train)
    val_f1.append(f1_val)
    test_f1.append(f1_test)
    
    # In ra train, validation, v test F1-score theo C
    print('max_depth: {:3} | train f1: {:5} | val f1: {:5} | test f1: {:5}'.
          format(depth, round(f1_train, 2), round(f1_val, 2), round(f1_test, 2)))

max_depth:   1 | train f1:  0.75 | val f1:  0.73 | test f1:  0.69

max_depth:   5 | train f1:  0.94 | val f1:  0.87 | test f1:   0.7

3.4. Vẽ biểu đồ train/val/test F1-score theo max_depth¶

In [ ]:
fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize = (12, 8))

# V biu  train F1-score theo cc gi tr max_depth
ax.plot(depths, train_f1, 's--', label = 'Train error', color = 'blue', linewidth = 2)

# V biu  validation F1-score theo cc gi tr max_depth
ax.plot(depths, val_f1, 's-', label = 'Val error', color ='green', linewidth = 2)

# V biu  test F1-score theo cc gi tr max_depth
ax.plot(depths, test_f1, 's-', label = 'Test error', color ='purple', linewidth = 2)

# V ng thng ng ng vi best max_depth
ax.axvline(best_max_depth, 0, 1, color = 'r', label = f'Max validation F1-score at max_depth = {1}')

ax.set_xlabel('Value of max_depth', fontsize = 15)
ax.set_ylabel('F1-score', fontsize = 15)
ax.set_ylim([0, 1])
ax.legend(loc = 'lower left', fontsize = 16)
ax.set_title('F1-score', fontsize = 20)
ax.set_xscale('log')
plt.tight_layout()
plt.show();

4. Model selection cho Decision Tree Classification dùng phương pháp cross validation¶

6.1. Chia dữ liệu¶

In [ ]:
# Chia d liu thnh 2 tp train_val v test set vi t l 80/20
X_train_val, X_test, y_train_val, y_test = train_test_split(
oh_X,y, test_size = 0.2, random_state = 1)

6.2. Dùng cross validation cho model selection¶

In [ ]:
import numpy as np
from sklearn.linear_model import Lasso
from sklearn.model_selection import KFold
from sklearn.metrics import f1_score

depths = [1, 2, 3, 5, 10, 15]

K = 5
kf = KFold(n_splits = K, shuffle = True, random_state = 1)
X=oh_X.values

mean_train_f1s = []
mean_val_f1s = []
mean_test_f1s = []

for depth in depths:
    train_f1s = []
    val_f1s = []
    test_f1s = []
    for train_index, test_index in kf.split(X, y):
        
        # split data theo train_index v test_index
        X_train, X_test = X[train_index], X[test_index]
        y_train, y_test = y[train_index], y[test_index]

        # To model theo max_depth
        dtree = DecisionTreeClassifier(max_depth = depth)
        
        # Fit the model trn train set
        dtree.fit(X_train, y_train)
        
        # Predict trn train, val, v test set
        y_train_pred = dtree.predict(X_train)
        y_val_pred = dtree.predict(X_train_val)
        y_test_pred = dtree.predict(X_test)
        
        # Tnh train, val, v test F1-score
        train_f1 = f1_score(y_true=y_train, y_pred=y_train_pred,average="macro")
        val_f1 = f1_score(y_true=y_train_val, y_pred=y_val_pred,average="macro")
        test_f1 = f1_score(y_true=y_test, y_pred=y_test_pred,average="macro")
        
        # Thm train v test F1-score vo cc list tng ng
        train_f1s.append(train_f1)
        val_f1s.append(val_f1)
        test_f1s.append(test_f1)
    
    # In ra train, validation, v test F1-score theo max_depth
    print('max_depth: {:6} | mean(train_f1): {:6} | mean(val_f1): {:6} | mean(test_f1): {:6}'.
          format(depth, round(sum(train_f1s)/5, 2), round(sum(val_f1s)/5, 2), round(sum(test_f1s)/5, 2)))
    
    # Thm train, validation, v test F1-score vo cc list tng ng
    mean_train_f1s.append(sum(train_f1s)/5)
    mean_val_f1s.append(sum(val_f1s)/5)
    mean_test_f1s.append(sum(test_f1s)/5)
